		<slide>
			<title>
				<line>Part III: Use Cases</line>
				<line>Design Philosophy</line>
			</title>

			<ul>
				<li><strong>Student-facing tone:</strong> clear explanations, minimal jargon, and helpful transitions.</li>
				<li><strong>Scaffolded learning:</strong> checkpoint questions, summaries, and “quick reference” sections in every chapter.</li>
				<li><strong>Interactive thinking:</strong> figures, slope fields, and numerical explorations are integrated into the narrative.</li>
				<li><strong>Pedagogical consistency:</strong> each method follows a labeled, step-by-step structure for easy comparison.</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				The goal: make the text feel like a guided conversation, not a wall of text or a lecture transcript.
			</p>
		</slide>

